33 ff. Horace adopted that form of the story according to which the bull vanished on reaching Crete, and Europa was left alone for a short time until Zeus reap- peared in his proper form. While alone she comes to herself and breaks out in sels-reproaches.— centum . . . potentem oppidis: the Homeric Κρήτη ἑκατόμπολις.

34 ff. pater: her first word re- minds her that by her folly she has lost a daughter's right to ap- peal to her father for protection. —filiaez genitive defining nomen. —furorez folly.
